olive oil
3 clove garlic
1 carrot
1 packet green beans
1 packet oyster sauce
1 tbs soy sauce
½ tbs sesame oil
¼ cup water
1 packet sweet chilli sauce
1 packet Shredded Cabbage Mix
2 packet pork mince
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet udon noodles
1 packet parsley

• Boil the kettle. Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice carrot into sticks. Trim and chop green beans in thirds.
• In a small bowl, combine sweet chilli sauce, oyster sauce, the soy sauce, sesame oil and water.

Little cooks: Take the lead by combining the sauces!

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook carrot until tender, 5-6 minutes.
• Add shredded cabbage mix and green beans and cook, tossing occasionally, until softened, 2-3 minutes. Transfer to a medium bowl.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook pork mince, breaking up with a spoon, until just browned, 3-4 minutes.
• Add garlic and sweet soy seasoning and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• While the pork is cooking, half-fill a medium saucepan with boiling water. Cook udon noodles over medium-high heat until tender, 2-3 minutes.
• In the last minute of cook time, gently stir noodles with a fork to separate. Drain, rinse and set aside.
• Reduce the frying pan heat to medium, then add sweet chilli-oyster mixture, cooked veggies and udon noodles to the pork. Stir to combine, 1-2 minutes.

• Divide sticky Chinese-style pork noodles between bowls.
• Tear over parsley (see ingredients) to serve. Enjoy!